Class BatchQuery.QueryId

java.lang.Object
org.klojang.jdbc.BatchQuery.QueryId
Enclosing class:
BatchQuery<T>
public static final class BatchQuery.QueryId extends Object
Functions as an identifier for a persistent query result. A QueryId (or rather it string representation) is meant to be ping-ponged back and forth between client and server, for example via a URL query parameter and response header, respectively. On the server side it is used to instantiate a BatchQuery object, allowing it to identify and wrap itself around the query result.
